{"questionId":"9066335","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Ethyne, C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>2</sub>, reacts with oxygen in welding torches.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Ethyne reacts with steam.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>2</sub> (g) + H<sub>2</sub>O (g) → C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>4</sub>O (g)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Two possible products are:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/5980/4c.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"316\" height=\"190\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">State the name of product <strong>B</strong>, applying IUPAC rules.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">ethanal &nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9066335","referenceCode":"19M.2.hl.TZ2.1c(i)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"State the name of product B, applying IUPAC rules.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c(i)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry","10.2 Functional group chemistry","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}